{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make domestic abuse policies mandatory in all workplaces in England",
        "additional_details": "With domestic abuse awareness, training and a mandatory domestic abuse policy in place, employers can stronger support employees who disclose domestic abuse.\r\n \r\nWork for many is a safe haven, losing their financial independence makes them dependent on their abuser putting them in danger.\r\n\r\nA domestic abuse policy could help save lives but with only 5% of organisations doing this, it's not enough, it has got to be mandatory.",
        "background": "I lost my job as a result of domestic abuse. When I tried to explain to my employer what was happening at home, they didn't want to listen and sacked me.",
